  • Package netgame.fivecarddraw

    • Class netgame.fivecarddraw.PokerCard extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • suit

          int suit
          This card's suit, one of the constants SPADES, HEARTS, DIAMONDS, CLUBS, or JOKER. The suit cannot be changed after the card is constructed.

        • value

          int value
          The card's value. For a normal cards, this is one of the values 2 through 14, with 14 representing ACE. For a JOKER, the value can be anything. The value cannot be changed after the card is constructed.

    • Class netgame.tictactoe.TicTacToeWindow extends javax.swing.JFrame implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • state

          TicTacToeGameState state
          The state of the game. This state is a copy of the official state, which is stored on the server. When the state changes, the state is sent as a message to this window. (It is actually sent to the TicTacToeClient object that represents the connection to the server.) When that happens, the state that was received in the message replaces the value of this variable, and the board and UI is updated to reflect the changed state. This is done in the newState() method, which is called by the TicTacToeClient object.

        • board

          netgame.tictactoe.TicTacToeWindow.Board board
